<chapter id="introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>

<para>
&klinpopup; is a program with which you can send an receive windows popup messages
like with "net send" or <trademark class="registered">Windows</trademark>.
</para>
</chapter>

<chapter id="using-klinpopup">
<title>Using &klinpopup;</title>

<para>
The usage of KLinPopup is pretty straightforward. Use the menu items or icons to send new messages, reply or delete them.
</para>

<sect1 id="klinpopup-features">
<title>More &klinpopup; features</title>

<itemizedlist mark="opencircle">
<listitem>
<para>can start docked only</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>adjustable new message signaling</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>


</sect1>
</chapter>

